Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.25,0:01:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}人類如何瞭解未知{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}How does one come to know The Unknowable?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.02,0:01:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}人類需要什麼技能{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}What faculties must a man possess?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.83,0:01:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}自從人類發現鯨油{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Since it was discovered that whale oil{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.94,0:01:27.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}可以以前所未有的方式點亮我們的城市{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}could light our cities in ways never achieved before,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.29,0:01:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}全世界需求量暴漲{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}it created global demand.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.62,0:01:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}使人類向開始向{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}It had pushed man to venture further and further{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.44,0:01:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}海洋更深處冒險{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}into The Deep, Blue Unknown.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.21,0:01:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們不知道海洋的深度{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}We know not its depths,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.72,0:01:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}也不瞭解海洋堛漸耵哂\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}nor the host of creatures that live there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.62,0:01:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}怪物是否真的存在{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Monsters, are they real?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.94,0:02:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}或者這些故事只是讓我們對海洋隱藏的秘密有所敬畏{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Or do the stories exist only to make us respect the sea's dark secret?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:11.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}{\pos(78,200)}楠塔基特島\N馬薩諸塞州\N1850年二月{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.58,0:02:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}這個問題使我即苦惱又興奮{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}The question both vexes and excites me,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.94,0:02:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}也是我再次向您寫信請求一次會面的原因{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}and is the reason I've written you a second time to request a meeting.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.75,0:02:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}一次和您交談的機會 先生{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}A conversation with you, Sir,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.08,0:02:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我相信這會對我將要寫的小說有很大幫助{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I believe will serve me well for the novel I intend to write,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.64,0:02:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}小說暫且名為 白鯨記{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}currently entitled Moby Dick{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.06,0:02:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我期望您能考慮我的提議{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I hope you will reconsider my offer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.25,0:02:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}未知 我的想像力始終想冒險的地方{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}The Unknown, that is where my imagination yearns to venture.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.94,0:02:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}始終折磨我的問題是{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}And so, the question plagues me still:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.15,0:02:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}人類如何才能探索未知{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}How does a man come to know The Unknowable?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.69,0:02:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}此致 赫爾曼·梅爾維爾{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Sincerely, Herman Melville.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們打烊了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}We're closed!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.88,0:02:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}8點後不接客{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}No borders after eight o'clock.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.34,0:03:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你居然來了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You came.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.99,0:03:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}親愛的 有人來看你{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}There's someone here for you, My Love.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.60,0:03:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}湯姆·尼克森{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Tom Nickerson?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}赫爾曼·梅爾維爾{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Herman Melville.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.80,0:03:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們收到了你的來信{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}We received your letter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.75,0:03:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你要麼走投無路要麼是個傻子大老遠跑來楠塔基特{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You're either a desperate man or a fool to come all the way to Nantucket.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.99,0:03:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我的提議還在{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Well, my offer still stands.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.46,0:03:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}3個月的住宿換一晚的交談{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Three months'lodgings for a single night's talk.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.59,0:03:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}這是我所有的錢了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}It's all I have in the world.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.77,0:03:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}但我更願意看作是一次投資{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}But I'd prefer to think of it as an investment.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.29,0:03:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我想要你告訴我{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I want you to tell me what happened...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.84,0:03:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}埃塞克斯號發生了什麼{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}to the Essex.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.92,0:03:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你覺得發生了什麼{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Well,what do you think happened?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.42,0:04:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}有傳言埃塞克斯號{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}There are rumblings,rumors that the Essex...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.38,0:04:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你想要什麼 期望聽到什麼故事{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}What do you want?What story do you expect to hear?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.98,0:04:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}白鯨的故事{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}That of The Whale.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.22,0:04:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}埃塞克斯號擱淺了 有完整的報告{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}The Essex ran aground, there was a full inquiry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.21,0:04:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我覺得那份報告不是事實全部{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I believe the inquiry was less than truthful.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.44,0:04:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}滾出去{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Get out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.09,0:04:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}先生 你是埃塞克斯號上唯一的倖存者{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You are the last survivor or the Essex, Sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.81,0:04:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}如果你不說出來 誰還能講出事實{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}If you won't talk, who will?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.01,0:04:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你沒聽見我的話嗎 出去{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You do not hear me, leave now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.75,0:04:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你不能走 拜託 就一會兒  他沒心情談{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- You mustn't go, please, just take a minute...    He's in no mind to talk, and{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.14,0:04:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我不是大老遠來就是為了被羞辱和浪費時間{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I haven't come all this way to be humiliated and waste my time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.55,0:04:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}拜託了 梅爾維爾 先生{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Please, Mr. Melville,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.96,0:04:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}他從來不跟別人談論埃塞克斯號 包括我 從不{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}he won't talk about the Essex to me, to anyone... never has... never.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.33,0:04:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我一點都不瞭解他{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I don't know anything about him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}他的精神在受折磨 需要救贖{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}His soul is... in torment, and in need of confession.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.36,0:05:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}拜託了 請讓我和他談 拜託了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Please, just let me talk to him... please.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.52,0:05:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}親愛的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Love,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.59,0:05:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我覺得和這個年輕人談會對你有好處{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I believe it would do you good to talk to the man.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.21,0:05:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}不{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}No!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.89,0:05:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你聽著{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You listen well!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.44,0:05:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你酗酒要死的時候誰撐著這個家了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Who holds this place together while you drink yourself to death?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.68,0:05:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你必須和這個年輕人談{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You WILL talk with this man, as much as is necessary...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.44,0:05:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}才能保住你的錢{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}to keep the money.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.43,0:05:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你知道我們的處境 湯姆{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You know our circumstances, Tom.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.40,0:05:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我只說必要的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Only as much as is necessary.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:05:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我去拿威士忌{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I'll get whiskey.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.69,0:06:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我忘了在信奡ㄗ鴔痟蕈g是一名捕鯨手{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I neglected to mention it in my letter, but I was a whaler once.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}有過一次出航 新手{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}One trip. I mean... green hand.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.91,0:06:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}那麼你應該都經歷過了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}So, you've seen it all.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.13,0:06:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我妻子讀過你的書{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}My wife read your books.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.70,0:06:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}她很喜歡 很高興聽到{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- She enjoyed them. - Happy to hear it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.08,0:06:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}銷量很好 但我估計這個故事{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}They had good sales, but I think that THIS story{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.23,0:06:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}甚至能超過我銷量不錯的第一部小說{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}could surpass even the success of my first novel... which did quite well.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.01,0:06:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}又一個你的航海軼事{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Another of your seafaring yarns.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.94,0:06:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你聽說過霍索恩嗎 梅爾維爾先生{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Have you read Hawthorne, Mr. Melville?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.98,0:06:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}當下有一名作家 一個大作家{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Now, there's a writer, a great writer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.12,0:06:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}他是的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}He is.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.99,0:06:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}但他不在這兒 因為我自己的原因{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}But he is not here, and I am...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.40,0:07:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我在這兒{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}for my own particular reasons.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.67,0:07:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我會告訴你埃塞克斯號 我相信你會失望的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I'll tell you of the Essex, I believe you will be disappointed,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.01,0:07:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}但我說的每個字都是真實的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}but every word I say will be true.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.30,0:07:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}埃塞克斯號的故事就是兩個男人的故事{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}The story of the Essex is the story of two men...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.99,0:07:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}喬治·波拉德船長{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Captain George Pollard,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.55,0:07:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}和他大副 歐文·查斯{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}and his first mate, Owen Chase.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}歐文 你不能遲到{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Owen, you don't want to be late.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.22,0:07:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我會到那兒的 再說了 不能讓我們的女兒睡在破陋的房子媢鴽a{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I'll be there, besides, can't have our daughter sleeping under a leaky roof, can we?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.54,0:07:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你為什麼那麼肯定是女兒{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}What makes you so sure it's a girl?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.84,0:07:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}肯定是的 她會提醒我你這麼固執為什麼我還是愛你{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Well, it has to be, so she can remind me why I have to love you, and you being stubborn.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.06,0:07:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}如果是女兒她會更像你而不是我{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}If it's to to be a daughter she'll be a version of you, not me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.91,0:07:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}金髮而且一心想征服世界{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Blond locks and determined to conquer the world.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.28,0:07:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我想過了今天你會用那件外套換一套制服{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I suppose after today you'll be tradin' in that tunic for a uniform.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.21,0:08:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}沒錯 終於能離開這破地方去賺個區艾瑟 船長該住的房子了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}That's right, finally out of this patch of dirt for a captain's house in Quaise.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.74,0:08:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我不想住在周邊都是古板的鄰居的房子喎\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I don't need one of those houses in town with stuffy neighbors.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.92,0:08:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}這埵釣為魖悝畯怳@家三口居住的地方{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}There's plenty room here for the three of us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.96,0:08:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}有時候你的溫情真讓人受不了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Ya know, sometimes your kind heart and good nature is just unbearable.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.45,0:08:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}去做你的船長吧{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Go get your captaincy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.96,0:08:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}- 你下注 1美元9分{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- What's your bid? - One ninety.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.24,0:09:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我用2美元買到了一千加侖{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I've got a thousand gallons at two dollars!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.42,0:09:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我佔40份{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I'll take 40 shares.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.15,0:09:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}賣家 賣家 在這{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Seller, seller, over here!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.33,0:09:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}克雷斯拉回來了1600桶{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Criterion's back with a fine haul, 1600 barrels.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.18,0:09:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}倫敦市場新紀錄 50磅銀器換燈芯{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}A new record, 50 pounds Sterling for headmatter on the London market.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.75,0:09:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}早上好 查斯先生{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Good morning Mr. Chase.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.83,0:09:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}馬森先生 請進{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- Mr. Mason. - Come in, please.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.26,0:09:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我的合夥人 本傑明·福勒{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}My partner, Benjamin Fuller.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.36,0:09:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}早上好 先生 請坐{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- Good morning, Sir. - Do sit down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.50,0:09:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}查斯先生 我們希望你知道我們對你{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Mr. Chase, I do hope you realize how satisfied we are{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.54,0:09:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}為我們多年的工作有多麼滿意{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}with the work you've done for us over the years.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.97,0:09:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}謝謝 先生{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Oh, thank you, Sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.24,0:09:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們其中一艘船 埃塞克斯號{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}And one of our ships, the Essex{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.07,0:10:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}已經花大價錢修整好準備出海了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}has just be refitted at great expense and is to go to sea.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.77,0:10:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}因為在她身上花了大價錢{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Now, having made such an investment in her,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.95,0:10:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們希望確保她在最適合的人手喎\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}we want to be sure she's in the best possible hands.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.60,0:10:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}所以{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}So...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.51,0:10:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們很高興邀請你成為這艘船的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}it gives us great pleasure to offer you a position aboard her...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.97,0:10:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}大副{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}as first mate.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.81,0:10:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}大副 是的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- As first mate? - Uh-hum.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.23,0:10:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}馬森先生 你許諾過我上次出航帶回來1500桶的話{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Mr. Mason, you... you promised me command of a ship after my last voyage when{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.13,0:10:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}會讓我當一艘船的船長 你保證過的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I brought you back 1500 barrels, do you remember? You gave me your word.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.02,0:10:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}那個承諾要推遲了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}That promise must now be deferred.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.80,0:10:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}像別人一樣我們最近行情不好{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Like everyone else we've had a mean time recently.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.15,0:10:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我看不是{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Well, never on my watch.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.69,0:10:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}楠塔基特主宰了全球市場 這點不能變{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Nantucket now dominates the world market, that must not change.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.73,0:10:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}沒有時間來試驗{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}This is no time for experimentation.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.88,0:10:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}埃塞克斯號必須由喬治·波拉德指揮{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}The Essex will be captained by George Pollard,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.34,0:10:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}偉大的捕鯨家族的後裔{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}scion of a great whaling family.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.90,0:10:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}他的父親也是我們的老主顧{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}His father also happens to be our patron.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.46,0:11:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}血統 查斯先生 你可以有出色的航海技能{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Blood, Mr. Chase, you can have all the voyages under your belt you want{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.85,0:11:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}但血統還是更重要{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}but blood will always win out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.80,0:11:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}但是血統不會幫你的船裝滿油回來 馬森先生{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Yes, well, blood's not gonna fill the ship with oil, Mr. Mason.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.77,0:11:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}要成功指揮船 船長需要被人尊重 如果別人不尊重他怎麼辦{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}To successfully command, a captain needs respect, now, what if the men don't respect him?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你就要確保別人尊重他{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You will make sure that they do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.41,0:11:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}再見 先生們{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Good day, Gentlemen.{\r}
