Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.73,0:28:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}而且速度越來越快{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}and it's movin' faster than that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.29,0:28:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}讓它來吧 水手們在陸地上呆久變軟弱了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Let it come, the men are soft from months on land, they{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.59,0:28:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}他們需要一次洗禮 告訴他們工作開始了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}need a good baptism, let them know our work has begun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.60,0:28:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}如果我們不降帆並駛離 風暴一定會追上我們的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}If we don't shorten sail and bear off it'll catch us on the beam.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.93,0:29:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}查斯 我們繼續向前航行{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Chase, we will stand on.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.02,0:29:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}勞倫斯 繼續向前 繼續向前 長官{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- Mr. Lawrence, hold our course. - Holding course, Sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.43,0:29:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們這樣前行會追到只差半天的航程{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}We'll lose half a day running like that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.41,0:29:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們最後能趕上 如果我們的人{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}We'll scut the end of it, if the men can't{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.49,0:29:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}不能應付這樣的狂風 上帝也幫不了我們{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}handle a gust like this, then God help us all.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.56,0:29:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}固定好一切應付糟糕的天氣{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Best secure for heavy weather.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.33,0:29:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}準備好應付天氣 邦德 我們要駛向風暴了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Best prepare for weather, Mr. Bond, we're headed into a squall.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.75,0:30:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們必須降帆離開這 退下 查斯先生{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- We must fall off and run with it. - Stand down, Mr. Chase.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.35,0:30:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}勞倫斯 航向不變 航向不變 長官{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- Mr. Lawrence, hold your course. - Holding course, Sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.27,0:30:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}降帆 查斯{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Shorten the sails, Mr. Chase.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.91,0:30:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們要砍下那些帆{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}We need to cut those sails down!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.00,0:31:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}船掉頭 向陸地開{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Turn the ship, head for land!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.76,0:31:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}不 損壞已經造成了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}No, the damage is done!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.76,0:31:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}太晚了 太他媽晚了{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}It's too late, it's too god damned late!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.99,0:31:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們會撞上的{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}We'll be broadsided!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.15,0:31:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}抓牢{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Hold on!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.55,0:32:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}小心{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Look out!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.54,0:32:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}花花公子{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Mr. Joy!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.36,0:32:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們要割斷 我知道了 歐文{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- We have to cut away the... - I've got it, Owen!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.47,0:32:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我們要讓船擺正{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}We have to set her up right!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.91,0:33:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你說要見我 長官{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You wish to see me, Sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.41,0:33:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}明天六時 你召集船員{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}At six bells tomorrow, you will assemble the crew,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.06,0:33:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}告知他們我們將返回楠塔基特維修{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}inform them that we will be returning to Nantucket for repairs.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.05,0:33:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}然後你向他們道歉你干涉了船長的命令{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}You will then apologize to them for interfering with a captain's order{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.33,0:33:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}今天差點讓船上的每個人都為此喪命{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}which nearly cost the lives of every man on this ship today.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.07,0:33:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}什麼{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}What?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.67,0:33:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}返回到港口我會接受你的辭呈{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}I'll accept your resignation upon our return to port.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.68,0:33:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}就這些{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}That will be all.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.28,0:33:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}是你下命令楊帆的 長官{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}It was your order to set stuns'ls, Sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.03,0:33:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}命令沒問題 這些人需要鍛煉{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}That decision was sound, the men needed testing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.92,0:33:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你送他們進風暴{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}- You sent 'em into a storm? - That...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.18,0:33:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}那是幸運不好{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}was unlucky.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.81,0:34:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}不 這是缺乏航海經驗 責怪運氣只會顯得軟弱{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}No, it was bad seamanship, and blaming misfortune is just plain weakness.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.94,0:34:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你他媽的無禮 你知道你在和誰說話嗎{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Damn your impertinence! Do you know who you're speaking to?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.14,0:34:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}我是船長喬治·波拉德 波拉德{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}My name is CAPTAIN George Pollard. POLLARD!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.30,0:34:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}而你查斯先生 無論你衣袖上釘多少白鯨徽章{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}And you Mr. Chase, no matter how many whale pins you may have on your lapel,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.57,0:34:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}你不過是個農民的兒子{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}are nothing more than the son of a farmer,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.93,0:34:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}仗勢欺人才當上的長官{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}who's managed to bullying his way into an officer's tunic.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.42,0:34:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}滾出去{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Now, get out!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.06,0:34:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}不帶一桶油回港口是個錯誤 長官{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}To return to port without a single barrel of oil would be a mistake, Sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.09,0:34:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}和名字是波拉德或者查斯沒什麼關係{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}And not behoove a man whose name is Pollard... or Chase, for that matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.29,0:34:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}對我們來說最好是抓緊時間工作{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}And the best thing for both of us would be t'work all hours God sends us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.76,0:34:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}把船裝滿油一年之內回到家{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}Fill this ship with oil, and be home inside a year{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.77,0:34:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMicrosoft YaHei\bord1\shad0}然後各自分道揚鑣{\r}\N{\fs12\bord1\shad0}and rid of one another as quickly as possible.{\r}
